    "description": "Open a Zstandard-compressed file in binary or text mode, returning a file object. The file argument can be either a file name (given as a str, bytes or path-like object), in which case the named file is opened, or it can be an existing file object to read from or write to. The mode argument can be either 'rb' for reading (default), 'wb' for overwriting, 'ab' for appending, or 'xb' for exclusive creation. These can equivalently be given as 'r', 'w', 'a', and 'x' respectively. You may also open...",
